i used to remember my dreams every morning now i rarely remember them at all but when i do remember them my dreams were in black and white what does this mean it means either that your sleep is getting interrupted perhaps by something like sleep apnea or when you wake up your mind is already on the day ahead try remembering your dreams as soon as you wake up in the morning have paper and pencil on a nightstand to jot down your dreams as soon as you wake up if most mornings however you can't remember no matter how hard you try it is possible that you are not dreaming often and perhaps should consult a sleep clinic to find out why Sleep apnea Dream Insomnia Lucid dreaming Sleep Out-of-body experience 50 First Dates Avenue Q Haibane Renmei Diazepam Turiya The Shining (film) Narcolepsy Jon Secada Edgar Cayce Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Freddy's Dead: The Final Nightmare Parsifal Dream (DC Comics) Rapid eye movement Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Daylight saving time Sleep disorder Electroencephalography Hypnosis Urinary incontinence The Sandman (DC Comics Modern Age) Mathematician Sleep debt Animism Wake Island Jacob The Sandman: The Doll's House The Big Sleep Jennifer Parker Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Indiana Jones and the Emperor's Tomb Pencil Ekadasi Reality Finnegans Wake I Dream of Jeannie Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Under Milk Wood Psychosis I Have a Dream Respiratory rate Philosophical skepticism Nocturnal emission Sigmund Freud Frank Herbert Long-term memory Traditional animation Dreamlands Irna Phillips Silver Surfer Oneiromancy Apnea Mandukya Upanishad Enlightenment (Doctor Who) House of M Cliff Richard Quotation mark Wilhelm Reich Euthanasia Homer the Heretic Cluster headache Shaggy dog story Tefillin Histamine Nightmare The Matrix character names Canonical hours Muraqaba Person Nightmares (Buffy episode) Code 46 USS Alden (DD-211) Circadian rhythm Kurt Cobain The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Night terror Good Morning America Hip hop